            "answer_text": "Only if you are adding something new. If it was reviewed in 2008 and there have been many advances since then, yes, there is room for a new review. Or if the last reviewer did a poor job or you have a markedly different perspective on the topic, there is room for a new review. Just remember that a review paper should do more than simply summarise the literature on a topic: it should bring previous literature together in a way that adds new insight or uncovers new patterns. ",
